%N A397414 Triangle read by rows: T(1,1) = 2; for n > 1, 1 <= k <= n, T(n,k) is the smallest unused positive number that has a common factor with at least one term in row T(n-2) but has no common factor with any term in row T(n-1).
%C A397414 The sequence is a version of the Yellowstone permutation A098550 where the number of terms that must satisfy the common factor criteria increases by one for each group/row of terms. However, unlike that sequence, it appears that many numbers are never terms - after 50000 terms the numbers 6, 10, 12, 18, 20, 21, 24, 30 have not appeared.
%C A397414 For the terms studied the primes appear in their natural order.
%H A397414 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A397414/b397414.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A397414 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A397414/a397414.png">Image of the first 50000 terms</a>. The green line is a(n) = n.
%e A397414 The triangle begins:
%e A397414 2;
%e A397414 3, 5;
%e A397414 4, 8, 14;
%e A397414 9, 15, 25, 27;
%e A397414 7, 16, 22, 26, 28;
